data.title: Good Mexican Fare in Carlsbad
data.text: Our group of 20+ had a nice early Wednesday evening dining experience.  They had a long table set up for our group and the server, Anthony A, did an outstanding job of handling all the drink and entree orders.  He was friendly, courteous and attentive.  Food orders covered nearly everything on the menu and I heard nothing but positive comments.  My chili relleno ala carte was huge and delicious.  The kept the salsa and chip baskets filled and no one went away hungry.  Prices are very reasonable.

data.title: Great Chili Renenoe
data.text: Not expensive and well located, the food is great.  It is next to the Carlsbad Beach Hotel so we ate 3 or 4 meals there.

data.title: If you want a good experience...DON'T GO HERE!
data.text:
Let me begin by saying that much of my feeling about this restaurant are due to the horrible service we received, which is why I didn't give it the lowest ranking.
The mexican food, particularly for San Diego standards, was very average...at best.  Overpriced, small portions, and our server couldn't have been less helpful.  Finally gave up waiting for our server to finish his cerveza and got up to get myself silverware so I could eat my dinner.  Guacamole was not bad, but very small amount for the prize.  My wife disliked her margarita so badly that she actually sent it back, claiming it could not have been made with the top shelf tequilla that she ordered.  I don't even remember what anyone ordered, and it wasn't worth remembering. Sadly, an old restaurant that has lost it's family values to become a tourist trap.

data.title: Carnitas from the Gobi Desert; actually, not that moist.
data.text:
Now an institution in downtown Carlsbad at the corner of Coast Hwy and Village Drive, Norte is a large Mexican restaurant with bar.  We ordered carnitas, which should be moist and flavorful; slow cooked and then deep fried.  Instead, the meat was dry, tough, and flavorless.  The worst I have ever tasted.  We made the most of it, given that we were being treated to a birthday meal, but even wrapped in a tortilla with beans, avocado, and salsa, the dry meat was not disguised. 

Why the second star?  Our host enjoyed their entree, the beans were good, and the servers pleasant.

Why not three?  The coffee was International House of Pancakes bad, the chips stale, the salsa weak and runny, and the place could have been cleaner.

Go elsewhere.

data.title: Good happy hour
data.text: This is a good place for happy hour margaritas with friends. We did eat dinner here once before and it was ok, not my favorite but keep in mind I'm a vegetarian so definitely makes it a little more challenging. Salsa is very mild and this place is good if you don't care for much spice in your food. Like I said, more of a happy hour on the patio place in the quaint Carlsbad village. Parking can be a challenge!

data.title: Good Happy Hour
data.text: Happy Hour is from 4-6 and is in the bar or on the patio. A limited menu is available for Happy Hour. The house margarita is good. My husband and I split a platter of mini tacos, chimichangas, flautas, and quesadillas. Although it was an appetizer, it was plenty of good for 2 people as a dinner (unless you are very hungry).

data.title: Norte a must for Happy Hour
data.text: The patio connected to the bar is a fun place to be. They have a wonderful happy hour menu (also, they have a complete menu and inside dining room). They have painted and decorated Norte's to give a cantina feel. The help is fun and energetic. The patio has a nice view of the Carlsbad Inn courtyard. Just a happy place to be and relax for a drink and appetizer (or dinner).

data.title: Stick w/taco bell
data.text: We ate at this restaurant during our vacation. The outdoor atmosphere is good. The weather was perfect and we enjoyed sitting outdoors. The taco I ate was horrible. The meat was dry and overlooked. I'm. Not sure exactly what the problem was. I had a chicken taco. The meat was hard and shredded but stick together. The appetizer chips were stale. We were disappointed.

data.title: Taste of Mexico - Tex-Mex
data.text: Great atmosphere inside or outside on the patio facing the ocean. Good cocktails/margaritas and chile relenos. Crispy fresh warm chips and good salsa. Have a great time in the bar too. Lot's of wide screen TV's.

data.title: Excellent food and great margaritas
data.text: We will definitely be back.  We are touring the area and this was an excellent find! Great patio with a fun atmosphere.

data.title: Our favorite local Mexican restaurant!
data.text: We love dining on the patio because the atmosphere is amazing.  You can eat outside year-round because of Carlsbad's mild climate (plus they have heaters).  Delicious food and good service!

data.title: Fidel Norte
data.text:
Good Mexican food for a fair price.  I like the salsa or hotsauce on the table.  Although is not especially hot, I enjoyed.

Their chicken and beef dishes are all outstanding,  I opted for a beef burro and chicken enchilada combo.

Great place for groups and families.  Have a large nice bar area as well.

data.title: good food
data.text: They have a special lunch that includes margaritas.  There is outdoor seating. I really liked the food.

data.title: Huge Nacho orders
data.text: We got an order of nachos to munch during the 1st presidential debate....our order came in a 8 x 10 pan and was totally yummy! We went back the next afternoon for a lunch of Mexican soups, which were very good. Recommend eating here.

data.title: Worst Mexican Food I Have Ever Had
data.text: As soon as I tried the  corn chips and salsa, we should have left.  Chips were as hard as fragments of plastic and tasted so stale.  Salsa was more like spiced, watery tomato juice.  When I complained, the waiter brought fresher chips.  My companion, a vegetarian, asked what is used to fry them.  Lard!  I haven't seen ard-fried chips in a restaurant in years.  In further questioning of the waiter, we were told that the only items on their menu that do not have lard are their plain, whole boiled pinto beans or a plate of vegetables with cheese. By then, it was too late for us to leave to look for another restaurant, so he ordered a simple burrito of flour tortilla filled with those boiled beans.  The chef thoughtfully included some lard-fried chips on the plate...which my companion brushed off.  My own combination plate had to be returned to the kitchen because the food was barely warm.  They obviously put it in the microwave briefly to reheat it, but when I cut into the chile relleno, a small rectangular block of white cheese fell out.  The cheese was still cold and not at all melted. The meat in my burrito was so salty that I left half of it.  With so many good Mexican restaurants in the area, I do not hesitate to tell visitors....dine someplace else!

data.title: A nice location with respectable food
data.text: We dined here twice on this trip.  The setting is very traditional with the old California adobe feel.  The service is very good, and the food is reasonable.  It's a good place to go with friends to have casual conversations in a setting that takes us back to the 60's beach cantinas.

data.title: Great place to relax
data.text:
We stayed for a long lunch into dinner and didn't feel rushed out. It was nice to relax in the beach weather, have a Margarita and enjoy the day. The asada burrito was excellent. Crab enchilada and tacos are also good. 
The afternoon happy hour deal is the margarita and it is likely the most popular drink. 
The patio is the place to stay unless you want to watch a sporting event, then you can stay inside the bar area.

data.title: Pleasant atmosphere outdoors
data.text:
Would suggest outdoor dining unless you prefer darker sports bars.
Beer is served cold with frosted mugs. Of course, Mexican food is good and plentiful

data.title: Nice Patio - OK Food
data.text: Norte has one of the most enjoyable patios in Carlsbad Village.  Unfortunately the food was not as good as it's been in past years.  It seems like the menu has been pared down as well.  We also had some difficulty getting properly made top shelf Margaritas.  But...if you have time...Happy Hour is GREAT.  The $4 house margarita is pretty good and there's free chips and salsa.

data.title: Great place to have too much fun ; )
data.text: They make super delish margaritas and the vibe was really fun. It didn't really feel like a tourist place but I'm sure we were not the only ones there. What makes this place fun is the open air feeling throughout...I don't think there is a bad seat in the place. The bartenders were super cool and put up with me and my sister as we had way too much fun! I had shrimp tacos, they were okay...not great but decent enough, especially if you are just eating to stay sober enough to act right ; )
